With thousands of QA interactions generated daily, manual evaluation was not scalable or consistent. Traditional metrics like BLEU and ROUGE were also insufficient â€” they fail to detect hallucinations, ignore meaning, and penalize useful variations.

This led us to build a new hybrid evaluation framework â€” combining deterministic metrics for consistency with LLM-based semantic judgment for nuance and trustworthiness.




â€œWe use deterministic metrics like a filter. If an answerâ€™s almost identical to the ground truth, we call it correct without LLM review. Only edge cases or uncertain answers go to the LLM. That gives us smarter evaluation with a lot less compute


